                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 31: Market regulator Sebi has clarified that its recent order barring brokerage firms from taking irrevocable authorisation to operate clients accounts does not cover settlement dues arising from past trades. Such revocation shall not be applicable for any outstanding settlement obligation arising out of the trades carried out prior to receiving request for revocation of the power of attorney, Sebi said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 31: The US-based unit of drug maker Sun Pharma has received a warning letter from health regulator US Food and Drug Administration for violation of good manufacturing practices regulations, the company said.                            
	 Calcutta, Aug. 31: Parle Agro, owned by Prakash Chauhan, is expanding its food and beverage footprint in the east. The maker of fruit juice drink Frooti and packaged drinking water Bailley plans to introduce snack food products in the eastern market from its new plant in Barasat, Bengal.
                                                                                                                          
